This paper deals with a method of quantifying preferences and reasoning about user preferences, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses improving the efficiency of outcome dominance testing, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of CP-nets to represent preferences is related to decision making (cs.DM) and computational economics (cs.CE).
